Citation.sAbstract: Molar heat capacities,C_P,123 and C_P,mix, have been measured for the ternary ochlorotoluene (1) + tetrahydropyran (2) + benzene or toluene or o-xylene (3) and their binaries tetrahydropyran (1) + benzene or toluene or o-xylene (2) at 298.15, 303.15 and 308.15 K. From the experimental results, excess heat capacities, C_P,123^E and C_P,mix^E values are calculated and fitted to Redlich-Kister equation to determine binary and ternary adjustable parameters along with standard deviations. The observed excess heat capacity data have been analyzed by utilizing topology of the constituent molecules (Graph theory). The estimated excess heat capacity values from Graph theory are in agreement with experimental values. The interaction parameters for binary mixtures (simulated by Graph theory) have been discussed to obtain information about molecular interactions in mixtures.
Citation.sTitle: Heat capacities of binary and ternary mixtures containing o-chlorotoluene, cyclic ether and aromatic hydrocarbons
sKeyword: Connectivity parameter of third degree, Interaction energy parameter
